  <!-- BUYER'S GUIDE -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Buyer's guide</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">How to choose the right <span class="accent">blog automation tool.</span></h2>
      <p>If you're not sure which tool fits your situation, or you're evaluating options outside this list, here's the decision framework we'd use ourselves.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Decide how much of the pipeline you want to hand off</h4>
              <p>If you want to eliminate all blog work (keyword research, writing, publishing), only theStacc, Journalist AI, and SEOWriting.ai qualify. If you want to write faster but still stay involved, Surfer, Jasper, or Writesonic are appropriate.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Calculate true per-article cost at your target volume</h4>
              <p>$9/month tools that limit you to 5 articles aren't cheap — they're $1.80/article at their stated volume limit. Always calculate cost per article at the volume you actually need, not the entry price.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Verify CMS compatibility before committing</h4>
              <p>Many tools only support WordPress. If you're on Webflow, Ghost, Wix, or a custom CMS, your options narrow quickly. theStacc and Journalist AI have the broadest CMS coverage on this list.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Match the tool to your publishing strategy — volume vs. quality</h4>
              <p>If your strategy is "publish 1,000 long-tail pages," Byword or Autoblogging.ai make sense. If your strategy is "publish 30 high-quality articles per month and rank them," theStacc's focus on quality and full pipeline automation is the better fit.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Consider whether blog automation is part of a broader organic strategy</h4>
              <p>Blog content alone doesn't complete your SEO. If you also need Google Business Profile automation and social media, theStacc's bundle (Blog + Local + Social, 15% off) eliminates the need to stitch together three separate tools.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

